Key message: comparison of trust in New Zealand Police and trust in New Zealand politicians shows relatively high and growing confidence in the police with relatively lower and declining confidence in politicians.
To better understand differences in trust of the New Zealand Police (Fig4.a) and trust in New Zealand Politicians, we can graph both trends side-by-side. Doing so reveals that rising trust in the police is not the result of a generic increase in institutional trust, but is a unique phenomenon that holds across a diverse population.


